===Etymology===
{{named-after|occ=Renault engineer|Pierre Bézier|wplink==|lang=en}} who popularized the curves developed earlier by {{w|Paul de Casteljau}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|mathematics|computer graphics}} A [[parametric]] curve defined by a set of [[control point]]s, two of which are the ends of the curve, and the others determine its shape. Bézier curves are applied e.g. in [[computer graphics]] to produce smooth, infinitely scalable curves. {{defdate|from 1960s}}

